  "diagnostic_reasoning": "The combination of lost power, rough idle, and hard starting points to issues in the fuel, ignition, or engine mechanical systems. A common carburetor issue causing rough idle and hard starting is a leaking power valve or incorrect idle mixture, often indicated by the idle mixture screws needing to be nearly seated (Source 2, 13, 22, 24). Hard starting and rough running can also be caused by a malfunctioning choke (Source 4, 13, 22, 55) or a lack of proper spark from the ignition system (Source 15, 44). A malfunctioning PCV system can also cause a rough idle (Source 13, 24, 36). I need to differentiate between these primary suspects.",
